{
  "stem": "4710.1",
  "chunk_idx": 6,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 4.8,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 44,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "And there was war in northern Africa.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 44,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "I remember I used to make drawings, how the Allied troops stand and where the German troops.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 44,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "I was very much aware and very much conscious about-- about-- about the war and what's happening around us.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 44,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "But Hungary itself was like a little island.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 44,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "We-- we felt that we are safe there, because, especially in our town, even the war has not made much changes in our life.",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 45,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "All kinds of regulations about food.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 45,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Certain foods went on rationing.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 45,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "That was also not [INAUDIBLE] so much an agricultural country.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 45,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And what became the refugees, refugees started coming from Poland, Slovakia, and they brought bad news what's happening to the Jews in Poland.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 46,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Well, what I remember as a child, they-- they were not talking a lot.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 46,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "But I realized it that they were sort of saved, saved from a-- from a bad fate, from the general community, the Germans are just killing the Jewish people there and-- we had-- we had even a cousin who escaped from Slovakia who lived in Bratislava.",
      "word_count": 46
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 46,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "It was not so much talk, especially in front of the children what is going on, when my uncles have been taken away from Slovakia.",
      "word_count": 25
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 46,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And-- but I-- the fear was already felt.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 46,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "It was in the air.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 46,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And of course, I understood it that it's-- we are in danger.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 47,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Hungarian.",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 48,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Strictly Hungarian.",
      "word_count": 2
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 49,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "No.",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 49,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "No Yiddish.",
      "word_count": 2
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 49,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "I haven't spoken at home Yiddish, though when I learned at cheder and later on in yeshiva, the language of the instruction was Yiddish.",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 49,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And gradually, I got to learn the language.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 49,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "But as not a-- not so much as a living language.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 49,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "It's more like an academical language for the study of the Talmud.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 50,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Always in Hungarian.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 51,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Well, you have to believe it.",
      "word_count": 6
    }
  ],
